"It is a very beautiful image - adds the psychologist - and reminds us that the sense of peace is dialogue, listening to each other. And the context also counts, even at these levels: I believe that in that place, on this day, peace is breathed, you still read the message of Pope Francis that was precisely centered on dialogue. These two lonely leaders who speak, while the world watches them with anguish after years of this terrible war, are the image of dialogue in what is a little 'house of peace'. There is no violence, I speak and you listen and vice versa." &nbsp;
